# Supabase (VPS self-hosted), Database, and Vercel

FuelBot’s backend is **self-hosted Supabase on the VPS** — not Supabase Cloud.

| What | URL |
|------|-----|
| **API (Kong)** | `https://fuelbot.lucas-dev-server.tech` |
| **Studio** | `https://studio.fuelbot.lucas-dev-server.tech` |

No SSH tunnel. No `mcp.supabase.com`. No `supabase link` to a cloud project ref.

See **[docs/SUPABASE_SETUP.md](../../docs/SUPABASE_SETUP.md)** for full details.

## 1. Studio (schema + data)

**Use Studio when:** Applying migrations, browsing tables, running SQL, checking data.

- **SQL editor:** `https://studio.fuelbot.lucas-dev-server.tech/project/default/sql/new`
- **Versioned migrations:** SQL files in [`supabase/migrations/`](../../supabase/migrations/) — paste into Studio and run (or use combined files like `RUN_IN_STUDIO_*.sql`).
- Do **not** tell the user to use Supabase Cloud dashboard or Cloud MCP.

## 2. App connection (React + local scripts)

**Use env + `@supabase/supabase-js` when:** Writing or changing application code.

- **Frontend (Vercel + local):** `VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://fuelbot.lucas-dev-server.tech` and `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- **Local scripts/imports only:** `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in `.env.local` — never in Vercel client bundle

## 3. Vercel

**Use Vercel for:** Hosting the frontend.

- Set `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` and `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` to the **VPS** values
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is **not** required on Vercel for the static app

## 4. Edge Functions (VPS)

Legacy functions live in [`supabase/functions/`](../../supabase/functions/). Deploy/run on the **VPS stack**, not Supabase Cloud.

## Summary

| Task | Use |
|------|-----|
| Apply migration DDL, inspect tables, ad-hoc SQL | **Studio** (`studio.fuelbot.lucas-dev-server.tech`) |
| React app queries / auth / RLS | **App env** (`VITE_SUPABASE_*`) |
| Import scripts, admin bypass RLS | **Local** `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` |
| Deploy frontend | **Vercel** |

Run `npm run audit:supabase` to verify env files point at the VPS API URL.
